  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Surgisis Anal Fistula Plug study is a clinical trial conducted in Saudi Arabia to study
      the safety and effectiveness of the Surgisis AFP Plug in the treatment of chronic anal
      fistulas.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Up to 30 patients will be treated with the Surgisis Anal Fistula Plug using a standardized
      surgical procedure to plug their anal fistula. Patients will be followed periodically until
      their 12-month follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
